{META_DATA}: "THE SHINING."
{META_DATA}: Post Production Script.
{META_DATA}: A STANLEY KUBRICK FILM
{META_DATA}: EXECUTIVE PRODUCER:
{META_DATA}: JAN HARLAN
{META_DATA}: PRODUCED AND DIRECTED BY: STANLEY KUBRICK
{META_DATA}: July, 1980
{META_DATA}: "THE SHINING."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COLORADO MOUNTAIN (U.S.A.) - DAY - L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lake and Mountains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TRACKS FORWARD past island in lake.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ROAD - DAY - L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: High Angle V.W. Car moving along road - CAMERA TILTS UP with it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COLORADO MOUNTAINS & ROAD - DAY - L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mountains and Road - V.W. Car moves away along road - CAMERA TRACKS after it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: L.S. V.W. Car moving away along road - CAMERA TRACKS after it and passes car - TRACKING FORWARD to Mountains in b.g.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.L.S. High Angle V.W. Car moves away along road - CAMERA TILTS UP with it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Car goes into tunnel and comes out other side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TRACKS after car.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: L.S. V.W. Car moves along road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TRACKS after it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mountains in b.g.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: L.S. High Angle V.W. Car moving away along road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mountain in b.g. CAMERA TRACKS after car.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: L.S. Mountain - CAMERA TRACKS IN on Hotel.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Black Frames.
{META_DATA}: THE INTERVIEW.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 2.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OVERLOOK HOTEL/LOBBY - DAY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack walks L-R across Lobby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TRACKS BACK & PANS with him to RECEPTIONIST behind desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, I've got an appointment with Mr. Ullman.
{DIALOGUE}: My name is Jack Torrance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RECEPTIONIST
{DIALOGUE}: His office is the first door on the left.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK moves away R-L.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA PANS with him and TRACKS IN after him through Secretary's office to open door of ULLMAN's office - revealing ULLMAN seated at desk with SECRETARY standing beside him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Ullman?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Yes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Jack Torrance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, well - come on in Jack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ULLMAN stands up and hands book to SECRETARY, walking round side of desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK moves into office.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TRACKS IN after him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shakes hands with ULLMAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Very nice to meet you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Nice to meet you, Mr. Ullman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ULLMAN points to SECRETARY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: This is my secretary, Susie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECRETARY
{DIALOGUE}: Hallo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Susie, how do you do?
{META_DATA}: 3.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Have any trouble finding us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, no problem at all.
{DIALOGUE}: I made the trip in three and a half hours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, that's very good time, very good.
{DIALOGUE}: Please sit down a minute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ULLMAN points to chair cam.R.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK sits cam.R.f.g.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ULLMAN walks behind desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: JAck, just make yourself at home.
{DIALOGUE}: Would you like some coffee?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, if you are going to have some, I wouldn't mind.
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Susie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECRETARY
{DIALOGUE}: Sure.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, and would you ask Bill Watson to join us?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECRETARY
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, I will.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ULLMAN sits behind desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUSIE walks forward to R.f.g.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. APARTMENT BUILDING/BOULDER - DAY - L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Apartment Building - cars parked in front of it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mountain in b.g. CAMERA TRACKS IN on Apartment Building.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JACK & WENDY'S APARTMENT IN BOULDER (USA) / LIVING ROOM - DAY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DANNY is sitting at table eating a sandwich.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WENDY sitting cam.R reading book.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Mom...
{META_DATA}: 4.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Do you really want to go and live in that hotel for the winter?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, Danny, it will be lots of fun.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I guess so.
{DIALOGUE}: Anyway, there's hardly anybody to play with around here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I know.
{DIALOGUE}: It always takes a little time to make new friends.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. DANNY eating sandwich.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I guess so.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. WENDY
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: What about Tony?
{DIALOGUE}: He's looking forward to the hotel, I bet.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. DANNY while eating sandwich wiggles forefinger of his L.hand and speaks with different voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: NO, I ain't Mrs. Torrance.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. WENDY
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: Oh come on, Tony.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't be silly.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. DANNY wiggles forefinger of L.hand and speaks with different voice.
{META_DATA}: 5.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to go there, Mrs. Torrance.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. WENDY
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: Well, how come you don't want to go?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. DANNY wiggles forefinger of L.hand and speaks with different voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: I just don't.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. WENDY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{DIALOGUE}: Well, let's just wait and see.
{DIALOGUE}: We're all gonna have a real good time.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OVERLOOK HOTEL/ULLMAN'S OFFICE - DAY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK over ULLMAN seated at desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILL WATSON enter office.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK rises and shakes hands with him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Bill, I'd like you to meet Jack Torrance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WATSON
{DIALOGUE}: How do you do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Bill, how do you do?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WATSON
{DIALOGUE}: Pleased to meet you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Pleasure to meet you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Grab a chair Bill, and join in.
{META_DATA}: 6.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WATSON & JACK sit down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Jack is going to take care of the Overlook for this winter.
{DIALOGUE}: I would like you to take him around the place as soon as we are through.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WATSON
{DIALOGUE}: Fine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Jack is a schoolteacher.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Eh - formerly a school-teacher.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WATSON (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: What line of work are you in now?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a writer um... Teaching has been more or less a way of making ends meet.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. WATSON.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WATSON
{DIALOGUE}: Well this ought to be quite a change for you.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, I'm looking for a change.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Our people in Denver recommended Jack very highly, and, for once, I agree with them.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN
{META_DATA}: 7.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Let's see, where were we?
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: I was about to explain that eh... our season here runs from oh May 15th to October 30th and then we close down completely until the following May.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Do you mind if I ask why you do that?
{DIALOGUE}: It seems to me that the skiing up here would be fantastic.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, it sure would be
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: but the problem is the enormous cost it would be to keep the road to the Sidewinder open.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a..
{DIALOGUE}: It's a 25 mile stretch of road - gets an average of 20 feet of snow during the winter, and there's just no way to make it economically feasible to keep it clear.
{DIALOGUE}: When the place was built in 1907, there was very little interest in winter sports, and this site was chosen for its seclusion and scenic beauty.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.L.S. ULLMAN over WATSON & JACK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, it's certainly got plenty of that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK laughs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: That's right.
{DIALOGUE}: And did they give you any idea in Denver about what the job entails?
{META_DATA}: 8.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Only in a very general way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...the winters can be fantastically cruel, and the basic idea is to...to cope with the very costly damage and depreciation which can occur.
{DIALOGUE}: And this consists mainly of running the boiler, heating different parts of the hotel on a daily rotating basis, repairing damage as it occurs and doing repairs, so that the elements can't get a foothold.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, that sounds fine to me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ULLMAN grunts off.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Physically, it's not a very demanding job.
{DIALOGUE}: The only thing that can get a bit trying up here during the winter is eh... the tremendous sense of isolation.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, that just happens to be exactly what I'm looking for.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm eh... I'm outlining a new writing project, and eh...
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: 9.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: five months of peace is just what I want.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: That's very good Jack, because eh... for some people eh solitude and isolation...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: can of itself be a problem.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Not for me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: How about your wife and son?
{DIALOGUE}: How do you think they'll take to it?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: They'll love it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Great...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, before I turn you over to Bill, there is one other thing I think we should talk about.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to sound melodramatic, but it is something that's...
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: 10.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: been known to give a few people second thoughts about the job.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I'm intrigued.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't suppose they eh told you anything in Denver about the tragedy we had up here during the winter of 1970?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK shakes his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe they did.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. BILL WATSON.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, my predecessor in this job
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: hired a man named Charles Grady, as the winter caretaker.
{DIALOGUE}: He came up here with his wife and two little girls of about eight or ten.
{DIALOGUE}: And he had a good employment record, good references and from what I've been told, I mean, he seemed like a completely normal individual.
{DIALOGUE}: But at some point during the winter, he must have suffered some kind of a complete mental breakdown.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: 11.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: He ran amok and eh... killed his family with an axe,
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: stacked them neatly in one of the rooms in the West Wing, and then he um... then he put eh both barrels of his shotgun in his mouth.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN sitting behind desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: The police eh... they thought that it was what the old-timers used to call cabin-fever, a kind of claustrophobic reaction which can occur when people are
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: shut in together over long periods of time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, that is eh quite a story.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. ULLMAN laughs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, it is.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, it's still hard for me to believe that it actually happened here, but it did and eh... I think you can appreciate why I wanted to tell you about it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK.
{META_DATA}: 12.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Ah, I certainly can, and eh... I also understand why your people in Denver left it for you to tell me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK laughs.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: U.S. ULLMAN laughing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, obviously some people can be
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. JACK.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ULLMAN (OFF) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: put off by the idea of staying alone in a place where something like that actually happened.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{DIALOGUE}: Well, you can rest assured Mr. Ullman, that's not going to happen with me, and eg as far as my wife is concerned, I am sure she'll be absolutely fascinated when I tell her about it.
{DIALOGUE}: She's a confirmed ghost story and horror film addict.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BOULDER APARTMENT/BATHROOM - DAY - M.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shooting through open door - DANNY standing on stool at basin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Tony, do you think Daddy will get the job?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, he did.
{DIALOGUE}: He's gonna phone Wendy up in a few minutes to tell her.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BOULDER KITCHEN/LIVING ROOM - DAY - M.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WENDY back to camera washing dishes at sink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PHONE RINGS OFF.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She dries her hand and puts carton in fridge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then moves L-R into Living Room - CAMERA PANS with her.
{META_DATA}: 13.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She picks up telephone receiver.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Hello.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL - LOBBY - DAY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK leaning on counter at reception desk, speaking into phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, babe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{META_DATA}: (over phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, hon. How's it going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Great.
{DIALOGUE}: Look, I'm at the hotel and I still have an awful lot to go through.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think I can get home before nine or ten.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BOULDER APARTMENT/LIVING ROOM - DAY - M.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WENDY sitting on back of chair phone to ear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WENDY
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Sounds like you got the job?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL - LOBBY - DAY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JACK leaning on reception desk with phone to ear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JACK
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Right it's a beautiful place.
{DIALOGUE}: You and Danny are gonna love it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BOULDER APARTMENT/BATHROOM - DAY - M.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DANNY standing on stool by basin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is reflected in mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TRACKS IN on his reflection in mirror.
{META_DATA}: 14.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Tony, why don't you want to go to the hotel?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DANNY wiggles forefinger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: You do too know, now come on tell me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DANNY wiggles forefinger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Please...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DANNY wiggles forefinger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Now Tony, tell me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL - LOBBY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shooting towards doors of lifts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood gushes in from L.side of lift and in from corridors L. and R. of lift doors - surging towards camera.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL/CORRIDOR - M.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two Little GRADY girls holding hands.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL/LOBBY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood gushing in from corridors L-R of lift doors and surging towards camera.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 15.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BOULDER APARTMENT - M.C.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DANNY screaming.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL/LOBBY - M.L.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blood gushing in from corridors L-R of lift doors and surging forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The blood gushes up into camera lens causing black out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Now hold your eyes still so that I can see.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BOULDER APARTMENT/DANNY'S BEDROOM - DAY - M.S.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOCTOR bending over DANNY lying on top of his bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is examining his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WENDY standing at foot of bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR
{DIALOGUE}: That's good, now the other one.
{DIALOGUE}: Good boy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOCTOR straightens up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts instrument away in case and closes it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then she sits on bed beside DANNY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR
{DIALOGUE}: Now Danny, when you were brushing your teeth, do you remember if you smelled anything funny, or saw any bright flashing lights, or anything at all strange?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. DANNY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR (OFF)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you remember when you were brushing your teeth?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 16.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. DOCTOR sitting on bed beside DANNY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WENDY standing at foot of bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR
{DIALOGUE}: What's the next thing you remember after you were brushing your teeth?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. DANNY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Mommy saying, 'Wake up, wake up, wake up Danny, wake up.'
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.S. DOCTOR sitting on bed beside DANNY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WENDY standing at foot of bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR
{DIALOGUE}: Now Danny, can you remember what you were doing just before you started brushing your teeth?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. DANNY
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DANNY
{DIALOGUE}: Talking to Tony.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.S. DOCTOR
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOCTOR
