{DIALOGUE}: Airports are shut down stranding thousands of passengers.
{DIALOGUE}: Highways are blocked by snowdrifts.
{DIALOGUE}: Railroad tracks are frozen.
{DIALOGUE}: Officials in Colorado tell Newswatch at least three people have been killed by exposure to freezing winds.
{DIALOGUE}: The Governor of Colorado is expected tomorrow to declare a weather emergency.
{DIALOGUE}: The National Guard might be called out to clear streets and roads.
{DIALOGUE}: Weather forecasters predict more snow and heavy winds tonight and tomorrow, with temperatures dropping well below zero.
